  "ai_usage": "A reference for pairing fonts WITHOUT web-font downloads. Define --font-head and --font-body as system stacks and apply to headings/body. Principles shown: contrast families (serif heading + sans body), or stay in one family with weight contrast. Prefer system stacks for performance; only add a web font when brand truly requires it (then preload + font-display: swap). Copy a card's two stacks as your tokens.",
  "path": "effects/typography-systems/font-pairings.html",
  "source": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n  <title>Font Pairings</title>\n  <script type=\"application/json\" id=\"effect-meta\">\n  {\n    \"id\": \"font-pairings\",\n    \"title\": \"Font Pairings\",\n    \"summary\": \"Reference combinations of heading + body fonts using only system font stacks.\",\n    \"description\": \"Shows several tasteful heading/body pairings (serif display + sans body, geometric + humanist, monospace accent) built from cross-platform system font stacks so they need no web-font downloads.\",\n    \"theme\": \"typography-systems\",\n    \"categories\": [\"typography\", \"fonts\", \"reference\"],\n    \"tags\": [\"font-pairing\", \"system-fonts\", \"serif\", \"sans\", \"monospace\", \"stacks\"],\n    \"tech\": [\"css\"],\n    \"era\": \"timeless\",\n    \"difficulty\": \"beginner\",\n    \"dependencies\": [],\n    \"browser_support\": \"All browsers (system font stacks resolve per OS).\",\n    \"performance_notes\": \"System fonts = zero network cost and no layout shift. The fastest possible typography.\",\n    \"accessibility_notes\": \"System stacks respect user/OS font settings. Ensure adequate size and line-height for readability (1.5 for body).\",\n    \"customization\": [\n      { \"name\": \"--font-head / --font-body\", \"description\": \"The paired stacks\", \"default\": \"see each card\" }\n    ],\n    \"variations\": [\"Swap a system stack for a self-hosted web font\", \"Add a --font-mono for code\", \"Pair weights, not just families, within one superfamily\"],\n    \"related\": [\"type-scale\", \"fluid-typography\"],\n    \"ai_usage\": \"A reference for pairing fonts WITHOUT web-font downloads. Define --font-head and --font-body as system stacks and apply to headings/body. Principles shown: contrast families (serif heading + sans body), or stay in one family with weight contrast. Prefer system stacks for performance; only add a web font when brand truly requires it (then preload + font-display: swap). Copy a card's two stacks as your tokens.\"\n  }\n  </script>\n  <style>\n    * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n    html, body { margin: 0; height: 100%; }\n    body { background: #0b0d12; color: #e7ebf3; padding: 1.2rem; overflow: auto; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; }\n    .pair { border: 1px solid #262c3d; border-radius: 14px; padding: 1.1rem 1.3rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; background: #11141c; }\n    .pair h3 { margin: 0 0 .2rem; font-size: 1.6rem; }\n    .pair p { margin: .2rem 0 .5rem; color: #b7bdcc; line-height: 1.5; }\n    .pair code { font-size: .68rem; color: #8b93a7; font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; }\n    .p1 h3 { font-family: Georgia, \"Times New Roman\", serif; }\n    .p1 p { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; }\n    .p2 h3 { font-family: \"Trebuchet MS\", \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -.02em; }\n    .p2 p { font-family: Georgia, serif; }\n    .p3 h3 { font-family: ui-monospace, \"Cascadia Code\", monospace; }\n    .p3 p { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"pair p1\">\n    <h3>Editorial Serif</h3>\n    <p>Serif display over a clean sans body — classic, trustworthy, great for long-form reading.</p>\n    <code>head: Georgia, serif · body: system-ui, sans-serif</code>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"pair p2\">\n    <h3>Modern Geometric</h3>\n    <p>A bold geometric sans heading paired with a serif body for an unexpected, refined contrast.</p>\n    <code>head: Trebuchet MS, sans-serif · body: Georgia, serif</code>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"pair p3\">\n    <h3>Technical Mono</h3>\n    <p>Monospace heading signals a developer/technical product; sans body keeps it readable.</p>\n    <code>head: ui-monospace, monospace · body: system-ui, sans-serif</code>\n  </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n"
}
